duck: housekeeping definition: the management of a house and home affairs.
Housekeeping is the act of cleaning the rooms and furnishings of a home.

wiki.text:
'Housekeeping' refers to the management of duties and chores involved in the
running of a household. It is also used to refer to the money allocated for such
use.<ref name=oxford>[http://oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/housekee-
ping?q=housekeeping "housekeeping"] [[Oxford Dictionary of English|Oxford
Dictionaries Online]]. Retrieved 2 June 2013.</ref> By extension, an office or
organization, as well as the maintenance of computer storage systems.<ref>[http-
://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/housekeeping?showCookiePolicy=t-
rue "housekeeping"] [[The Collins English Dictionary]]. Retrieved 2 June
2013.</ref>

A housekeeper is a person employed to manage a
household,<ref>[http://oxforddictionaries.com/definition/english/housekeeper
"housekeeper"] [[Oxford Dictionary of English|Oxford Dictionaries Online]].
Retrieved 2 June 2013.</ref> and the domestic staff. According to [[Mrs Beeton's
Book of Household Management]], the housekeeper is second in command in the
house and "except in large establishments, where there is a house steward, the
housekeeper must consider herself as the immediate representative of her mistre-
ss".<ref>[http://ebooks.adelaide.edu.au/b/beeton/isabella/household/chapter2.ht-
ml#chapter2 Mrs Beeton's Book of Household Management] Web version of the book
at the University of Adelaide Library. Retrieved 2 June 2013.</ref>
